{"submission_id":"sub_d371f52d65d9c1ef","run_id":"2026-07-13_codex_ace-december-2025-warning-cohort-curation","submitted_at":"2026-07-13T17:11:47.921Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:d371f52d65d9c1efa856b8a1fc789a058b728d4194b895f43659b8e50a345323","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001","observation_kind":"project","local_observation_id":"project_ace_b60_b68_m57_warning_cohort_2025_12_08","create_new":true,"label":"B60/B68/M57 ACE warning-phase cohort — December 8, 2025","raw_text":"The MTA expanded the Automated Camera Enforcement (ACE) program to three additional bus routes. On December 8, the B68 and B60 in Brooklyn and the M57 in Manhattan entered a 60-day warning phase, during which vehicles that blocked bus lanes, bus stops, or double-parked received warning notices. These routes joined 51 already covered by ACE. Since its launch in June 2024, the program has extended across all five boroughs, equipping more than 1,400 buses and covering 560 miles of service, benefitting over 915,000 daily customers. The MTA reported that ACE has improved reliability and stabilized travel speeds, underscoring the importance of keeping bus lanes clear to deliver faster, more dependable service for New Yorkers.","payload":{"project_name":"B60/B68/M57 ACE warning-phase cohort — December 8, 2025","project_type":"bounded ACE warning-phase activation cohort","project_family":"enforcement_program","status":"implemented","document_time_status":"implemented","implementation_date":"2025-12-08","description":"Bounded ACE cohort for B60, B68, and M57 beginning with the official 60-day warning-phase activation on December 8, 2025; it does not assert a fine-bearing start date.","date_normalized":"2025-12-08","date_precision":"day","date_source_field":"implementation_date","implementation_date_normalized":{"raw_text":"2025-12-08","normalized_date":"2025-12-08","precision":"day","confidence":"submitted_iso"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001","evidence_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001#p010_c0011","source_path":"raw/sources/nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001/blocks.jsonl","page_number":10,"block_id":"p010_c0011","text_sha256":"sha256:e147dfa103fac9d1499e269c62864619e13cdfd4b3540e71e98ebfb706cd1a42","text_source":"raw_text","role":"warning_phase_activation","source_quote":"On December 8, the B68 and B60 in Brooklyn and the M57 in Manhattan entered a 60-day warning phase"},{"source_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001","evidence_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001#p011_c0009","source_path":"raw/sources/nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001/blocks.jsonl","page_number":11,"block_id":"p011_c0009","text_sha256":"sha256:2d2318454276de1fad6ef39bbd54826456515f6b382b2a9e95ab426545adf858","text_source":"raw_text","role":"warning_phase_definition","source_quote":"lanes, bus stops, or double-parked received warning notices"},{"source_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001","evidence_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001#p001_c0002","source_path":"raw/sources/nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0002","text_sha256":"sha256:1c2e7d7242d4937bffeb7ae2ac5b4071b084298424eb1637e9c216f6f292d64f","text_source":"raw_text","role":"report_month_context","source_quote":"December 2025"},{"source_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001","evidence_id":"nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001#p003_c0003","source_path":"raw/sources/nyct_key_performance_metrics_doc194001/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0003","text_sha256":"sha256:da018863a9eae42e35f1a801fc448de9d224d07d24d389b5c264e09564cfb624","text_source":"raw_text","role":"report_date_context","source_quote":"December 15, 2025"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[],"warnings":["project.project_family is runner-owned normalized output; submit the raw source literal and let the runner populate this companion.","project.document_time_statu